    "body": "## Problem\r\nquickfix lists lack a way to get counts of each error type in O(1) time. currently, items must be iterated through programatically, which is O(N) and slow for very large lists.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nmaintain a type-frequency histogram in 'qf_list_T' and expose it via the 'total' key in getqflist() and getloclist().\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\nAI-assisted: OpenCode (Gemini 3 Flash)\r\n\r\nwhy is this here and not a planned vim-patch?: because i wrote this for nvim first and then tried to port to vim, but i couldn't get past a buffer overflow error that i don't know how to debug. (help is appreciated!)",
